==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English '''heven''' < Old English '''[[heofon]]''', possibly < Proto-Germanic '''[[*khemina-]]''' < Proto-Indo-European base '''[[*kem-]]'''/'''[[*kam-]]''' ("to cover").

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: hĕv'ən
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈhevən/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /<tt>"hev@n</tt>/

===Noun===
#The sky.
#(''theology'') The [[paradise]] of the [[afterlife]] in certain [[:w:religion|religions]].
# The home of the [[god]] or the [[deity]].
#: ''Mommy's gone to '''heaven''' to be with '''God'''.''
# A place that is [[infinite]] in every way; the Kingdom of God.

====Synonyms====
*(sky): [[firmament]], [[sky]]

====Antonyms====
*(paradise): [[hell]]

